heres what i got from a dream dictionary:
rape
Something or someone is jeopardizing your self-esteem and emotional well-being. You feel that someone or something is being forced upon you. 
sex
You need to be more receptive and incorporate aspects of your dream sex partner into your own character. Alternatively and a more direct interpretation of the dream, may be your libido's way of telling you that it's been too long since you have had sex. It may indicate repressed sexual desires and your needs for physical and emotional love.
love
Dreaming of love of being in love, suggests intense feelings carried over from a waking relationship. It implies happiness and contentment with what you have and where you are in life. On the other hand, you may not be getting enough love in your daily life. 
crush
Dreaming that you have a crush on somebody, is a literal reflection of your attraction and fascination for that person. Seeing your crush in your dream, represents your current infatuation with him or her. 
torture
   Dreaming that you are being tortured indicates that you are feeling victimized or helpless in some relationship or situation.

Mommy was nice enough to bring me home an article dated DEC 20th BEFORE THE MOVIE CAME OUT. about Peter Pan, yet it was so dreadful. I read it over, and it remarked "And in place of the usual innocence, there's palpable sexual chemistry between the commitment-phbic peter, Played by the bare chested hunky-american Jeremy, and Wendy portrayed by a 13 year old british newcomer, Rachel Hurd-Wood.'The camera displays an obsession with the enormous permently wet lips of wendy' wrote film critic John walsh, In londons The Independent." On the other hand they did argue the title of the article, "I dont think there is anything creepy about first love, I think it is one of the most beautiful things about the play[originally written by J.M barrie in 1905] Wendy is also intrigued by Cpt. Hook, and he knows this and plays off it. I really wanted it to be the original story and not all sweet and light. I think it is a surprise to people because they are so used to the 1953 version which did remove all darkness. We want to protect kids from the world, but they are sharp. They can see whats around them and they know there are dark things out there- and want stories to explain those things to them"

I was mostly disgusted about how the writers of this article really put the movie down before it was in theatres, discouraging people to go see it with their children, and i dont think it was their place. I do think it is a beautiful story about love and admitting to your weakness, and i also agree Rachel and Jeremy had so much sexual tension, and that they in turn may be true loves to each other. I dont think any kids could act that good without it being natural, as if you truely did love them. It is my most favorite movie-ranks same to Pirates Of the Caribbean, and it makes me cry everytime i see it. But i dont beleive it has any sex in it that children, 5,6 years of age, would rather notice.

        Love <33
Katie
